        <abstract> 
<p>He has finished MEW’s work on hybrid willows [<hi rend="italic">Die Bastardbefruchtung im Planzenreich</hi> (1865)] and sends his thanks. The extreme frequency of hybrid willows is new to CD, and he finds the explanation of their numbers in certain locations ingenious.</p> 
            <p>Comments on the criticism of Gärtner’s view of reversion</p>
            <p>and the differences between MEW and Naudin.</p>
            <p>CD now has doubts regarding his own view that hybrids are sterile from not being perfectly accommodated to their conditions of life.</p>
        </abstract>
